 piece of fake UI that is intended to mimic "},{"code":"PKAddPaymentPassViewController","type":"codeVoice"},{"type":"text","text":". That class is restricted to apps with a special entitlement from Apple, and as such can be difficult to build and test against. This class implements the same public API as "},{"code":"PKAddPaymentPassViewController","type":"codeVoice"},{"type":"text","text":", and can be used to develop against the Stripe API in "},{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"testmode only"}],"type":"emphasis"},{"type":"text","text":". (Obviously it will not actually place cards into the user’s Apple Pay wallet either.) When it’s time to go to production, you may simply replace all references to "},{"code":"STPFakeAddPaymentPassViewController","type":"codeVoice"},{"type":"text","text":" in your app with "},{"code":"PKAddPaymentPassViewController","type":"codeVoice"},{"type":"text","text":" and it will continue to function. For more information on developing against this API, please see https:\/\/stripe.com\/docs\/issuing\/cards\/digital-wallets ."}],"navigatorTitle":[{"kind":"identifier","text":"STPFakeAddPaymentPassViewController"}],"title":"STPFakeAddPaymentPassViewController","role":"symbol","fragments":[{"kind":"keyword","text":"class"},{"kind":"text","text":" "},{"kind":"identifier","text":"STPFakeAddPaymentPassViewController"}],"kind":"symbol","type":"topic"}}}